-- China Aims to Cut Energy Use Per Unit of GDP by 17 Percent, News Reports
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-13T02:37:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-13/china-aims-to-cut-energy-use-per-unit-of-gdp-by-17-percent-news-reports.html
China aims to cut energy use per
unit of gross domestic product by 17 percent from this year over
the next five years, Shanghai Securities News reported, citing
an unidentified person involved in the drafting of a government
plan.  The Asian nation plans to cut carbon dioxide emissions per
unit of GDP by about 20 percent, the report said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
